import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='cx', y='cy', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cx and cy?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x="name", data=data, order=data['name'].value_counts().index)
    ax.set(xlabel='Name', ylabel='Frequency')
    ax.axhline(y=data['name'].value_counts().max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max Frequency: {:.2f}'.format(data['name'].value_counts().max()))
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x="variable", y="value", data=pd.melt(data[['cx', 'cy']]), ax=ax)
    plt.title('Are there any outliers in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Variable')
    plt.ylabel('Value')
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
